<h2>Why Growing Kenyan Retailers Outgrow WooCommerce and Shopify</h2>
<p>WooCommerce and Shopify are excellent starting points for <a href="/articles/ecommerce-website-development-kenya">online retail</a>. But as your business grows, more products, more orders, more complex requirements, these platforms begin to show their limitations.</p>

<p>Custom e-commerce development is the solution for Kenyan retailers who need a store that's built for their specific business, not a generic template adapted to fit.</p>

<h2>The Limitations of Off-the-Shelf Platforms</h2>
<h3>Performance Ceiling</h3>
<p>WooCommerce sites get slow as product catalogues grow. Every plugin added increases load time. On Safaricom 4G, the difference between a 2-second load and a 5-second load is significant, the 5-second site loses roughly 50% of its visitors before they see a single product.</p>

<h3>Plugin Dependency and Fragility</h3>
<p>A typical WooCommerce store might run 15–25 plugins. Every plugin is a potential security vulnerability and a point of failure. Plugin updates break other plugins. Themes become incompatible. This creates an ongoing maintenance burden that grows worse over time.</p>

<h3>Limited Customisation</h3>
<p>Shopify and WooCommerce theme systems constrain your UX to what the platform allows. Custom animations, unique product configurators, bespoke loyalty programmes, multi-vendor marketplaces, these require custom development, and doing custom development on top of a CMS is often more expensive than building custom from the start.</p>

<h3>Platform Lock-In</h3>
<p>With Shopify, you pay a monthly fee forever, you can't access your full codebase, and leaving is painful. Your business becomes dependent on Shopify's pricing decisions and feature roadmap.</p>

<h2>What Custom E-commerce Enables</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Native M-Pesa STK Push</strong>, built into the checkout, not bolted on via a third-party plugin</li>
  <li><strong>Custom product configurators</strong>, bespoke options, bundles, and pricing logic</li>
  <li><strong>Multi-vendor marketplace</strong>, allow multiple sellers under one platform</li>
  <li><strong>Integration with your ERP or inventory system</strong>, real-time stock sync</li>
  <li><strong>Loyalty and rewards programmes</strong>, fully custom logic, not limited by plugin rules</li>
  <li><strong>Subscription and recurring billing</strong>, MPESA recurring payments (M-Pesa Ratiba)</li>
  <li><strong>Bulk and wholesale ordering</strong>, customer-specific pricing tiers</li>
</ul>

