<h2>The Business Case for Custom</h2>
<p>Consider a Kenyan retailer doing 200 orders per month. If their WooCommerce store has a 3% conversion rate on 5,000 monthly visitors, they get 150 orders. A custom store achieving 4.5% conversion on the same traffic gives 225 orders, a 50% increase in revenue from the same ad spend, the same traffic, just a faster, better-designed store.</p>
<p>At an average order value of Ksh 3,000, that's an extra <strong>Ksh 225,000/month</strong>. The cost of a custom build pays for itself within weeks.</p>

<h2>When Is the Right Time to Go Custom?</h2>
<p>You're ready for custom e-commerce when:</p>
<ul>
  <li>You're doing more than 50 orders per month and want to scale</li>
  <li>Your WooCommerce/Shopify site is consistently slow and you've tried to fix it</li>
  <li>You need functionality that no plugin provides out of the box</li>
  <li>Plugin maintenance is taking more than 2 hours per month of developer time</li>
  <li>You've had a security incident on your WordPress site</li>
</ul>

